column2: 50 feet closer to shore on SW site.
First air temperature over 70 degrees- first I heard loon.
Weeds above the surface in some places.
Lily pads in bloom- 2 inches of rain in last few days.  Hummingbirds are nuts!
Water temp. =68 degrees air 73 degrees. 0.82 inches rain 2 days before.
No rain since last reading air temp. 68 degrees.
Air 60 degrees water at 3 feet = 63 degrees.  1.5 inches of rain since last dip.  Lily pads appeared 5/29.
2 feet deep at the end of the pier.
Three inches of rain last week.
Sample date-water dirty-air temp 82 F. ice out 4/13/99
Air temp 66 F. 5" of rain May 7- 8 + 9.  Water cleaner. only 3 water temps because windy + in a rowboat. hummingbirds are here.
Another 1.8" of rain. air temp 66 F.
Air temp 75 F. 0.5" of rain 3 hours prior.
Another 3.57" or rain since last measure.
3.3" of rain in the past four days.
The air temperature is 79 degrees and it is very humid.
Air temp 68 F. too windy to keep boat in deep hole. weather cool.
Beautiful week - no rain. air temp 72 F.
Air temp is 62 degrees.  Ice out 4/3.  Geese and ducks 4/12.
3-4 days very warm- 80's.  Today air temp is 62 degrees.  1st humming birds.
4" of rain in last three weeks.
Rained 0.02" before sampling (date of satellite imagery) .
Collected chlorophyll and phosphorous samples today.
The air temperature is 68 degrees- hazy- D.O. not done because of the threatening storm.
Air temperature in the last five days.
Just received 1" of rain- the outlet keeps lake level immediately.
Air Temp is 50 degrees F. Ice on once 11/08/01 then again on 12/13/01 and then out on 4/21/02.
Air temp 49 degrees F. It has been a cold spring. Depth measured at the end of pier is 2.875 feet.
Air temp is 75 degrees F. Finally we have a summer.
Thunderstorms predicted for 6/7 and going out of town 6/8- so cannot take reading during satellite path (25) date.
Lake is turning green. Weather is hot and humid. Weeds are on the surface of the lake.
Satellite path 25 is today. Thunderstorms predicted for the next 3 days.
Satellite path 25 sensor due tomorrow but rain is forecasted.
First hard frost- rain predicted the next 3 days.
Satellite path 25 today- air temp is 44 degrees F.
Ice out 4/21/03. Spring has been seasonally nice.
Many strings of neon algae on surface.
Snowed last week.  1.0" precipitation. 9/9/03 water level so low that boat won't come off lift.
D.O. at 3 ft = 10 mg/l.  Too windy to do more.
Temp./D.O. profile equipment failure-- 15 ft D.O. taken 6/8/04 8 mg/l- at 21 ft 6/8/04 7 mg/l.
Outside temp 68 F.  Weather has been cool and windy.
Fair amount of neon algae today.
Cold air temps past week.  Highs in the 50s and 60s.
Ice out 4/13/2005.  Very cold last 2 weeks.
Miserable weather continues - high 40s- lows 30s.  Misty.  Less than 1" of rain.
Very hot - storm brought 0.75" of rain last night.
5 days of air temps in the 90s!
90s for a week - in the 50s overnight.  Specks of neon algae.
Cold and windy last 2 weeks.  1" snow on 5/12/06.
Cold wind from north 1 whole week.
Fair amount of neon algae floating.
Fair amount of neon algae present.  49 degrees last night.
Still significant amount of neon algae.
Neon algae - copios - cleared by 6 PM (from wind).  4+ inches of rain last week.
Algae disappeared.  Sent phosphorus and chlorophyll in.
4" of snow on pier.  Temp outside 43 F.
Couldn't get boat in until yesterday
Rained 0.45" in morning.  Note: equipment failure with temp./D.O. profile.
Sent in chlorophyll and phosphorus samples
10 feet of sand beach - never before.  Aquatic plants.
Got an inch of rain - 1st since mid July
No rain from 7/12 to 9/25.  7+ inches of rain sicne 9/26.
Ice out 4/26/2008.  Pier and boat put in yesterday.  Cold- windy spring.
Very cold + misty for  the last 2 weeks!! Very cold + misty for  the last 2 weeks!!
September was a wonderful with mild temps- but no rain.  October- so far has been unseasonably cold.
Ice out -my bay-south side of lake was 3/17/10

column1: April winds continuing thru first week of May.

column2: 5 inches of rain since May 28th Phosphorus + Chlorophyll samples to be mailed on 6/21

Lake has recieved 20.1 " of rain since 5/28/10. Water is like a bath tub with temp for the top 3 ft @ 70.9 temp F Recieved 20.1 invhes of rain since 5/28/10.  Temps are 79.1 to 66.5. Second week of hot humid weather!
Had another 3.5 " of rain............total of 29.1 since the end of May.  Noticed small amounts of blue-green algae........first time this summer!
Ice out 04/26/11  Having a very wintering spring.
Air temps up to 80's last few days.  Pine tree pollen all over. Air temps up to 80's last few days.  Pine tree pollen all over.
Last week was cool with temps in the 60's to low 70's.  This week  it is the 2nd day of temps in the mid 80's to low 90's with high humidities
Very warm March + ice out was 3/21/12 April broughrt the cold conditions back.

column1: I also had some boat problems so didn't to site til 4/14.  Phospherous sample was collected on/14 + kept in refridgerator til late Monday for mailing.  Snowing today [4/16]

column2: Air temps have been colder than normal...........20's during  the night
It suddenly got really windy + I was unable to get watertemp at 21 ft.
Path 25 today.  Clarity is much better than this time last year. Satellite path 25 today. Clarity seems much better than this time last year
Have had 4.1" of rain in the last 9 days.   Beautiful sunny day today
Very hot + humid stretch of 4-5 days.  storm on July 1 received 2 " of rain
weather is more seasonal..  Flecks of blue green algae present Weather more seasonal.  Flecks of blue-green algae present
Blue-green algae more noticeable More blue-green algae evident.
Lake more murky- but still good clarity in deep hole....crazy!  Mailed in phosphorous + clorophyll samples today.
urkiness to the right of my property more dense than last time.  Area from 20 feet east of my property to beyond campgroud- approximately 15 ft. f4rom sho0re.

column1: Not received rain  lately.....lajke level really down

column2: Lake level is down at least a foot.  Air temp todfay 72 degrees F
Ice off part of lake 5/8/13............my bay on 5/9/13.  Have had an inch of rain 2 days prior.  21 in more than  orf snow during the month of April!  A neighbor saw a male merganzer yesterday.
Cold + windy past 3-4 days ----lo's in the 30's...........hi's in the hi 50's tolo 60's
Almost 2" of rain in the last 10 days.........second dusting of pine pollen/heavty
Partly Cloudy-  Cold snap 2 days ago with lows in upper 20's
Clear Day- Upper 30's temp overnight- sufficient rain lately
Clear day... We were on vacation mid-month

Our sincere apologies - the last 3 days of July were extremely windy. August 1/2 were Sat. and Sunday. August 3- I didn't get off work until 5:00 p.m. and yesterday (8-4) was also windy. We are new to this and trying to do the best we can.
Sunny and calm- upper 80's last several days and dry
received 1" of rain yesterday- sunny today
Beautiful Day- Maples just starting to turn red
Slight wind.  No rain for a few days.
slight wind- partly cloudy. slight wind- partly cloudy.
